verses.roman:
nandinī, āra kāmadeva, caitanya-dāsa
durlabha viśvāsa, āra vanamāli-dāsa

synonyms: nandinī—of the name Nandinī; āra—and; kāmadeva—of the name Kāmadeva; caitanya-dāsa—of the name Caitanya dāsa; durlabha viśvāsa—of the name Durlabha Viśvāsa; āra—and; vanamāli-dāsa—of the name Vanamālī dāsa.
translation: Nandinī, Kāmadeva, Caitanya dāsa, Durlabha Viśvāsa and Vanamālī dāsa were the tenth, eleventh, twelfth, thirteenth and fourteenth branches of Śrī Advaita Ācārya.
